a design prototype or sitemap. Midway through, the client rejects the layout. Analyze
what went wrong in the process and how it should have been handled.
  The main problem here is that the developer rushed into coding without proper planning. Since no sitemap or design prototype was made, the client did not get a clear idea of how 
the website would look. Because of this, both the developer and the client had different expectations, and the client rejected the layout in the middle of the work.
This could have been avoided by first preparing a sitemap and a simple design prototype. These would help the client understand the structure and layout of the website before coding
starts preventing confusion and saving time and effort.

10. A university website was launched successfully, but after six months, students stopped visiting it because the exam schedules were outdated. Which phase of the development
lifecycle was neglected? Explain the activities involved in this phase.
   The phase that was neglected is the Maintenance phase. Even though the website was launched successfully, it was not properly updated afterward. Because exam schedules were outdated, 
students lost interest and stopped visiting the website.
The maintenance phase involves regularly updating content, fixing errors, and checking that all information is accurate. It also includes improving performance, updating security, and
making small changes based on user needs. Regular maintenance keeps the website useful, reliable, and trusted by users.
